yes it is, the way Wallace phrased his questions was terrible. Each time he asked a question the candidate would have to spend a minute rejecting the narrative of the question.  The questions are suppose to be given in a way that does not install it's own narrative.  Furthermore, he often debated the candidates back with non-factual positions.  For instance when he said the "military has been doing mail in ballots like this", that was blatantly false, the military does a system that resembles absentee ballots, not mass mail out ballots.

The difference is that Biden supports mail in ballots because they favor Democrats, and Trump doesn't because it doesn't favor Republicans and there is a lot of verifiable evidence that it's unreliable and will cause chaos during the election.
